data.title: Best sandwiches around
data.text: We have been getting sandwiches here for over 20 years. They are an independent family run place with great sandwiches and donuts.  Right off the freeway so you can grab lunch and head to the beach.

data.title: Not only Donuts but GREAT Sandwiches
data.text: Pull into this hidden away gem and grab a delicious sandwich that comes with a donut as a bonus.  Freshly made - fresh bread- YUM!  I highly recommend them, if you are planning on stopping on a school day at lunch time- order ahead and they will have it waiting for you.  Small - family run organization that is wonderful

data.title: Great sandwiches at excellent prices!
data.text:
Don't miss this Deli, offers great sanwiches and prices are unbeatable. I tried their hot beef sandwich and 'twas the best I had. Combo comes with fresh donuts! 👍
Located in Lapaz near I5.

data.title: Best pastries EVER!
data.text:
This family owned pastry shop starts in the morning with possibly the best pastries on the planet, big enough to share, but you won't want to. Then, as the day progresses, they switch over to making grilled sandwiches with desserts.  We make a point of going there every time we are in Southern California.

The staff is as sweet as the pastries.

data.title: Best kept secret
data.text: Best sandwhich ever. I ordered a tuna on rye toast with some of the many free extras that one can have and when it came it was a magnificent 3" high.  I was astonished that included in the price of $5.57 was a soda and a freshly baked donut.  I was more astonished to find out that they are open from 4:00 am until 5:00pm Monday to Saturday and from 5:00 am to 3:00pm on Sunday so there is no excuse not to try this place out. I also give it 10 out of 10 for cleanliness.  This place is not easy to find as it is tucked away, but is well worth the visit. It is just to the East of the I-5 past the junction with Muirlands Blvd.
